00:45:42.630 --> 00:45:45.800
So if you look at what
had been going on in Syria

00:45:45.800 --> 00:45:48.360
before this episode in Libya,

00:45:48.360 --> 00:45:51.310
what had been going on in Syria was

00:45:51.310 --> 00:45:56.070
several years of catastrophic
drought starting in 2007,

00:45:56.070 --> 00:46:01.000
and this had meant that
hundreds of thousands of farmers

00:46:01.000 --> 00:46:02.433
had lost everything,

00:46:03.630 --> 00:46:07.050
their crops had died,
their animals had died,

00:46:07.050 --> 00:46:09.160
just catastrophic droughts.

00:46:09.160 --> 00:46:10.440
And so what did they do?

00:46:10.440 --> 00:46:13.960
They went to the cities,
looking for non-existent work.

00:46:13.960 --> 00:46:18.930
And the Assad regime came to USAID,

00:46:18.930 --> 00:46:20.907
they came to the US saying,

00:46:20.907 --> 00:46:23.060
"We need help, we need assistance,"

00:46:23.060 --> 00:46:25.903
